# {{.Name}} — AI Coding Rules

## Project Structure

```
cmd/server/              Application entry point (env config loaded here)
internal/db/             Database connection + embedded migrations
internal/repo/           Data access layer (Store interface + PostgreSQL impl)
internal/web/            HTTP layer
internal/web/server.go   Route registration + middleware groups
internal/web/handler/    One package per domain (home, health, errors{{- if .IncludeAuth}}, auth{{- end}})
internal/web/components/ Shared templ components (layout, form helpers)
static/                  CSS, JS, images
```

## Handler Pattern

- One handler package per domain: `internal/web/handler/<name>/`
- Constructor injection: `NewHandler(store repo.Store, log *slog.Logger) *Handler`
- Route comments above methods: `// GET /path`
- Register routes in `internal/web/server.go`
- Use `respond.HTML`, `respond.JSON`, or `respond.Negotiate` for responses

## Validation

- Use `hamr/pkg/validate` — validators return `""` for valid, error string for invalid
- Two-level validation:
  1. **Blur**: HTMX `hx-post` to validate single field, return OOB swap
  2. **Submit**: Validate all fields, return 422 with form re-render
- Never validate in the repo/store layer

## Responses

- `200` for successful GET
- `303` (See Other) for redirects after POST (PRG pattern)
- `422` for validation errors
- Use `middleware.SetFlash()` before redirects for success/error messages

## CSS
{{- if eq .CSS "plain"}}
- Plain CSS with design system in `static/css/`
- Variables in `base/variables.css`, reset in `base/reset.css`
- Component styles in `components/`, layout in `layout/`, pages in `pages/`
{{- else}}
- Tailwind CSS — classes directly in templ components
- Config in `tailwind.config.js`
{{- end}}

## Testing

- Unit tests alongside source files: `*_test.go`
- Use `testify/assert` and `testify/require`
{{- if .IncludeE2E}}
- E2E tests in `e2e-go/` with `//go:build e2e` tag
- Run: `make e2e` (containerized) or `make e2e-local`
{{- end}}

## Database

- Migrations in `internal/db/migrations/` (sequential numbering)
- Use `sqlx` for queries in repo implementations
- Store interface in `internal/repo/repo.go`
